Photo: James Nielsen, Staff Image 82 of 82 John Legend sets Woodlands show 1 / 82 Back to Gallery John Legend spent Super Bowl week partying it up in Houston. And he'll return soon for a proper show.
The singer's Darkness and Light Tour includes a May 21 date at the Woodlands Pavilion. Tickets are $42.50-$102.50 and go on sale at 10 a.m. Friday.
ON THE CARPET: John Legend and other celebs at Club Nomadic in Houston
Legend's fifth album, "Darkness and Light," was released in December and features the hit "Love Me Now."
He's featured in the award-winning film "La La Land," which is poised to sweep the Oscars. Legend also sings a remake of the title track, alongside Ariana Grande, to the upcoming "Beauty and the Beast" live-action film.
